			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Lunate letters of plain form, getting smaller from line 1 to line 4; the fifth line is much larger and Agnello suggests a different hand. Alpha has straight bar throughout; Epsilon is mostly lunate but somewhat variable; zeta in form of straight Z; Kappa has detached arms; Mu in first instance has middle strokes joining very high, in second instance four equal length oblique strokes; xsi is vertical with three equal horizontals; omicron full size; pi straight strokes of equal length; rho rounded and closed; sigma lunate.</p>
