            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><supplied reason="lost">Φῆ</supplied>λιξ</name></persName> <choice><orig>χρητὸς</orig><reg>χρηστὸς</reg></choice> κα
                    <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">ἄμ</supplied>εμπτος ἔζησεν
                    <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">ἔτη</supplied> <choice><reg><supplied reason="lost">ἑ</supplied>πτὰ</reg><orig><supplied reason="lost">ἑ</supplied>ντὰ</orig></choice> μῆνες δ<supplied reason="lost">ύο</supplied>
                    <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">ἡμέρ</supplied>ας πέντε χαῖρε
                    <lb n="5"/><orig>ΠΡΙΑ</orig><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="2"/><unclear>Α</unclear><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="1"/><orig>ΡΗ</orig>                    <lb/><gap reason="lost" unit="line" extent="unknown" cert="low"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note>Text of Agnello</note>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="line 3"><note>In the drawing, NTA is clear, and alternative interpretations (a larger number in the tens) should be considered</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Felix, worthy and blameless, lived 7 years, 2 months five days. Farewell. ... </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The letters in the final line are larger, but it is not immediately clear from the drawing that they must be in a second hand (the assumption of Agnello is that they were written later). Judgement on this point, and the preferred reading of line 3 should be reserved until autopsy is possible.</p>
            </div>
